  tabs = '[
    {
      "id": "main",
      "name": "Main",
      "content": "For more details about Dependency-Track see the projects website at https://dependencytrack.org\n\nDependency-Track is an intelligent Component Analysis platform that allows organizations to identify and reduce risk in the software supply chain. Dependency-Track takes a unique and highly beneficial approach by leveraging the capabilities of Software Bill of Materials (SBOM). This approach provides capabilities that traditional Software Composition Analysis (SCA) solutions cannot achieve.\n\n[YOUTUBE]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=208W-pUOEU8[/YOUTUBE]\n\nAt a high-level, Dependency-Track takes inventory of all third-party and open source components, continuously monitors them for known security and license risks, and provides organizations the ability to quickly respond to new threats. Dependency-Track monitors component usage across all versions of every application in its portfolio in order to proactively identify risk across an enterprise.",
      "order": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "features", 
      "name": "Features",
      "content": "- Consumes and produces CycloneDX Software Bill of Materials (SBOM)\n- Consumes and produces CycloneDX Vulnerability Exploitability Exchange (VEX)\n- **Full-stack component support for:**\n  - Applications\n  - Libraries\n  - Frameworks\n  - Operating systems\n  - Containers\n  - Firmware\n  - Files\n  - Hardware\n  - Services\n- Tracks component usage across every application in an organizations portfolio\n- Quickly identify what is affected, and where\n- **Identifies multiple forms of risk including:**\n  - Components with known vulnerabilities\n  - Out-of-date components\n  - Modified components\n  - License risk\n  - More coming soon…\n- **Integrates with multiple sources of vulnerability intelligence including:**\n  - National Vulnerability Database (NVD)\n  - GitHub Advisories\n  - Sonatype OSS Index\n  - VulnDB from Risk Based Security\n  - More coming soon.\n- Helps to prioritize mitigation by incorporating support for the Exploit Prediction Scoring System (EPSS)\n- Maintain a private vulnerability database of vulnerability components\n- **Robust policy engine with support for global and per-project policies:**\n  - Security risk and compliance\n  - License risk and compliance\n  - Operational risk and compliance\n- **Ecosystem agnostic with built-in repository support for:**\n  - Cargo (Rust)\n  - Composer (PHP)\n  - Gems (Ruby)\n  - Hex (Erlang/Elixir)\n  - Maven (Java)\n  - NPM (Javascript)\n  - NuGet (.NET)\n  - Pypi (Python)\n  - More coming soon.\n- **Identifies APIs and external service components including:**\n  - Service provider\n  - Endpoint URIs\n  - Data classification\n  - Directional flow of data\n  - Trust boundary traversal\n  - Authentication requirements\n- Includes a comprehensive auditing workflow for triaging results\n- Configurable notifications supporting Slack, Microsoft Teams, WebEx, Webhooks, and Email\n- Supports standardized SPDX license IDs and tracks license use by component\n- Easy to read metrics for components, projects, and portfolio\n- Native support for Kenna Security, Fortify SSC, ThreadFix, and DefectDojo\n- API-first design facilitates easy integration with other systems\n- API documentation available in OpenAPI format\n- OAuth 2.0 + OpenID Connect (OIDC) support for single sign-on (authN/authZ)\n- Supports internally managed users, Active Directory/LDAP, and API Keys\n- Simple to install and configure. Get up and running in just a few minutes",
      "order": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "integrations",
      "name": "Integrations", 
      "content": "## CI/CD Integration\n\nDependency-Track provides extensive integration capabilities for modern software development workflows:\n\n### Build Tool Integration\n- **Maven Plugin**: https://github.com/DependencyTrack/dependency-track-maven-plugin\n- **Gradle Plugin**: Native CycloneDX Gradle plugin support\n- **NPM Integration**: JavaScript/Node.js ecosystem support\n- **Python Integration**: pip and poetry support\n- **Docker Integration**: Container image scanning capabilities\n\n### CI/CD Platform Support\n- **Jenkins**: Official Jenkins plugin available\n- **GitHub Actions**: Community-maintained actions\n- **GitLab CI**: Pipeline integration examples\n- **Azure DevOps**: Extension available in marketplace\n- **TeamCity**: Plugin support\n\n### Security Platform Integration\n- **Fortify SSC**: Software Security Center integration\n- **ThreadFix**: Vulnerability management platform\n- **DefectDojo**: Application security management\n- **Kenna Security**: Risk-based vulnerability management\n\n### Notification Systems\n- **Slack**: Real-time notifications and alerts\n- **Microsoft Teams**: Team collaboration integration\n- **WebEx**: Enterprise messaging support\n- **Email**: SMTP-based notifications\n- **Webhooks**: Custom integrations via HTTP callbacks\n\n### Enterprise Systems\n- **LDAP/Active Directory**: Enterprise authentication\n- **SSO Solutions**: SAML and OpenID Connect support\n- **JIRA**: Issue tracking integration\n- **ServiceNow**: IT service management integration",
      "order": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "installation",
      "name": "Installation",
      "content": "Dependency-Track is distributed as Docker containers.\n\n## Docker Compose\n\n```bash\ncurl -LO https://dependencytrack.org/docker-compose.yml\ndocker-compose up -d\n```\n\n## Docker Swarm\n\n```bash\ncurl -LO https://dependencytrack.org/docker-compose.yml\ndocker swarm init\ndocker stack deploy -c docker-compose.yml dtrack\n```\n\n## Additional Installation Options\n\n### System Requirements\n- **Memory**: 4GB RAM minimum (8GB+ recommended)\n- **Storage**: 20GB available disk space\n- **Java**: OpenJDK 11 or higher\n- **Database**: PostgreSQL 10+ (included in Docker setup)\n\n### Network Requirements\n- **Outbound HTTPS**: Access to vulnerability data sources\n- **Port 8080**: Web interface (configurable)\n- **Port 8081**: API endpoint (configurable)\n\n### Configuration\nAfter installation:\n1. **Initial Setup**: Change default admin password (admin/admin)\n2. **Data Sources**: Configure vulnerability intelligence feeds\n3. **Teams & Permissions**: Set up user access controls\n4. **Notifications**: Configure alert channels\n5. **Integrations**: Connect CI/CD tools and scanners",
      "order": 4
    },
